### CST8917 Final Project - Version B (Logic Apps + Service Bus) - Test Scenarios
###
### In Version B, expense requests enter the pipeline by being SENT TO THE
### SERVICE BUS QUEUE `expense-requests`. The Logic App picks them up with
### its "When a message is received" trigger. This file shows two things:
###
###   (A) Direct-call tests against the validator Function (useful for unit-
###       testing validation logic in isolation).
###   (B) Instructions for submitting a message to Service Bus via the
###       Azure Portal / az CLI / Service Bus Explorer (that is what really
###       exercises the Logic App in production).

@validatorHost = http://localhost:7071
@functionKey   = REPLACE_WITH_LOCAL_OR_AZURE_FUNCTION_KEY

### ============================================================
### (A) DIRECT VALIDATOR TESTS
### ============================================================

### Scenario 1: Valid expense under $100 (no manager approval needed)
POST {{validatorHost}}/api/validate?code={{functionKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Ahmed Boudouh",
  "employee_email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "amount": 45.75,
  "category": "meals",
  "description": "Client lunch meeting",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### Scenario 2: Valid expense >= $100 (manager approval required)
POST {{validatorHost}}/api/validate?code={{functionKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Ahmed Boudouh",
  "employee_email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "amount": 350.00,
  "category": "software",
  "description": "Annual JetBrains license",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### Scenario 3: Missing required field
POST {{validatorHost}}/api/validate?code={{functionKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Ahmed Boudouh",
  "amount": 50.00,
  "category": "supplies",
  "description": "Pens and notebooks"
}

### Scenario 4: Invalid category
POST {{validatorHost}}/api/validate?code={{functionKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "employee_name": "Ahmed Boudouh",
  "employee_email": "ahmed@example.com",
  "amount": 75.00,
  "category": "entertainment",
  "description": "Team movie night",
  "manager_email": "manager@example.com"
}

### ============================================================
### (B) END-TO-END TESTS VIA SERVICE BUS
### ============================================================
### To run the actual Logic App end-to-end, publish a message to the
### `expense-requests` queue. Using az CLI (requires the Service Bus CLI
### extension installed via  az extension add --name service-bus):
###
###   az servicebus queue message send \
###     --resource-group rg-cst8917-final \
###     --namespace-name <your-sb-namespace> \
###     --queue-name expense-requests \
###     --body '{"employee_name":"Ahmed Boudouh",...}'
###
### Or paste the JSON body into Service Bus Explorer -> "Send messages".
###
### Test each of the 6 required scenarios by posting the six JSON bodies
### above to the queue:
###   1. Valid < $100                     -> auto-approved
###   2. Valid >= $100 + manager approves -> approved
###   3. Valid >= $100 + manager rejects  -> rejected
###   4. Valid >= $100 + no response      -> escalated (Logic App timeout)
###   5. Missing required fields          -> validation rejection branch
###   6. Invalid category                 -> validation rejection branch
###
### Monitor outcomes via:
###   - Logic App run history (approved / rejected / escalated filters fire)
###   - Service Bus topic subscriptions (expense-approved, expense-rejected,
###     expense-escalated) - use Service Bus Explorer to peek messages.
###   - Employee notification inbox (Outlook connector).
